The Osun State Command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), has arrested three men for allegedly dealing in adulterated petroleum products. The Commandant of NSCDC in the state, Emmanuel Ocheja, paraded the suspects; Adeyeye Emmauel, Nasiru Adamu and Isa Mohammed at the Corps headquarters in Osogbo, the state capital. Ocheja said, the three suspects were arrested at Ibodi junction, Ilesa, with 19 jerricans of 25 liters of adulterated fuel. However, the suspects denied the allegation. Ocheja said the suspects would be charged to court to serve as a deterrent to others.